_{\\rm CME}$. The\nCME fraction is compatible with zero for the 30% most central events in both\nsystems and then becomes positive; averaging over the 0-70% centrality interval\nyields an upper limit of 2% (3%) and 25% (32%) at 95% (99.7%) confidence level\nfor the CME signal contribution to ${\\gamma_{\\alpha\\beta}}$ in Xe-Xe and Pb-Pb\ncollisions, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2022 12:46:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-28"}
