{"id":"2210.15440","submitter":"Efe Hamamc{\\i}","authors":"Mahmut Elbistan, Efe Hamamci, Dieter Van den Bleeken and Utku Zorba","title":"A 3+1 formulation of the 1/c expansion of General Relativity","comments":"45 pages + 3 appendices. Version accepted for publication in JHEP\n  with corrected typos in the appendix","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1007/JHEP02(2023)108","report-no":null,"categories":"gr-qc hep-th","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Expanding General Relativity in the inverse speed of light, 1/c, leads to a\nnonrelativistic gravitational theory that extends the Post-Newtonian expansion\nby the inclusion of additional strong gravitational potentials. This theory has\na fully covariant formulation in the language of Newton-Cartan geometry but we\nrevisit it here in a 3+1 formulation. The appropriate 3+1 formulation of\nGeneral Relativity is one first described by Kol and Smolkin (KS), rather than\nthe better known Arnowitt-Deser-Misner (ADM) formalism. As we review, the KS\nformulation is dual to the ADM formulation in that the role of tangent and\nco-tangent spaces get interchanged. In this 3+1 formulation the 1/c expansion\ncan be performed in a more systematic and efficient fashion, something we use\nto extend the computation of the effective Lagrangian beyond what was\npreviously achieved and to make a number of new all order observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2022 14:05:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2023 06:27:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 30 Mar 2023 14:54:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-31"}
